references: The statistics for all the datasets are shown in Table 1. Our pre-processing technique adheres to recognised principles, such as treating ratings as implicit, using all interactions without regard to the rating value, and deleting users and things with fewer than 5 interactions (Kang and McAuley, 2018; Sun et al., 2019). For testing, as in (Kang and McAuley, 2018; Sun et al., 2019). For testing, as in (Sun et al., 2019; Kang and McAuley, 2018), we keep the most recent interaction for each user, while for validation, we keep the second to last action. The remaining interactions are added to the training set, which is the only one affected by the fake users perturbation.
